I'll try the data_processing_parser again with explicit format parameter to ensure JSON input.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {
    "format": "json"
  }
}</tool_call>

Now that the data is parsed, I'll proceed with the data_processing_filter tool to filter the data.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {
    "format": "json",
    "source": "data/input.json"
  }
}</tool_call>

            Next, I'll execute the data_processing_transformer tool to transform the filtered data.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "source": "data/input.json"
  }
}</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the computation_analyzer tool to analyze the transformed data.

<tool_call>computation_analyzer
{
  "options": {
    "source": "data/input.json",
    "format": "json"
  }
}</tool_call>

            Finally, I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool to validate the processed data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "data": "data/output.json",
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "metrics": {
        "type": "object"
      },
      "patterns_found": {
        "type": "number"
      },
      "confidence": {
        "type": "number"
      }
    },
    "required": ["metrics", "confidence"]
  },
  "options": {
    "format": "json"
  }
}</tool_call>
